				<LayoutObject hash="DE49A6C34B32D65C0C856706E3CADE73" id="16" type="Text" name="" kind="2">
					<SourceUUID>9B85736A-6604-4379-9E9B-438E74D45377</SourceUUID>
					<Bounds top="30" left="580" bottom="411" right="1030"></Bounds>
					<Options>1610612736</Options>
					<Text>
						<StyledText>
							<Data><![CDATA[# About this layout

- This layout is used by bitbucket pipeline to generate SaXML.
- The layout name must be SaXMLDeliveryExecutionContext.
- The layout must contain an xmlFile field.
- The layout table does not need to contain any records.

# FileMaker configuration

Per file:
- Install add-on (you don't need to apply the add-on to any layout)
    - This will create the following:
        - SaXMLDelivery table with xmlFile and other fields
        - SaXMLDeliveryExecutionContext layout with xmlFile and other fields
        - saxmlDelivery family of scripts
- Set up an account that can be used with the Data API ("fmrest" extended privilege)

Per server:
- Install a valid SSL certificate (required by the Data API)
- Enable the Data API

# Bitbucket configuration

- Set up a repository with a pipeline that calls fm-saxml-delivery
  - See https://github.com/soliantconsulting/fm-saxml-delivery
- You'll need to set up the appropriate environment variables in the repository
- Run the pipeline on a schedule and/or ad hoc]]></Data>
